/*!
\page opentrep-dbmgr
      Command-line utility to manage the SQLite3 database

\section sec_synopsis SYNOPSIS

<b>opentrep-dbmgr</b> <tt>[--prefix] [-v|--version] [-h|--help] [-p|--porfile <POR-file-path>] [-d|--database <Xapian-travel-database-path>] [-s|--sqlite <SQLite-database-path>] [-l|--log <path-to-output-log-file>]</tt>

\section sec_description DESCRIPTION

\e opentrep-dbmgr is a small program to manage the SQLite3 database.
   The file with the list of the ORI-maintained POR (points of reference)
   may be parsed, and the corresponding content inserted into the SQLite3 DB.

\e opentrep-dbmgr accepts the following options:

 \b --prefix<br>
    Show the Opentrep installation prefix.

 \b -v, \b --version<br>
    Print the currently installed version of Opentrep on the standard output.

 \b -h, \b --help<br>
    Produce that message and show usage.

 \b -p, \b --porfile <POR-file-path><br>
    Path (directory and file name) of the file of POR (points of reference).
	Usually, the file is ori_por_public.csv, for which the latest version
	may be found in the OpenTravelData project on GitHub:
	http://github.com/opentraveldata/optd/tree/trunk/refdata/ORI

 \b -d, \b --database <Xapian-travel-database-path><br>
    Path (directory) to the Xapian travel database.
	The indexer creates, or overwrites it when it already exists,
	the Xapian database. It materialises as a collection of data files
	within a directory usually named 'traveldb'.

 \b -s, \b --sqlite <SQLite-database-path><br>
    Path (directory) to the SQLite database.

 \b -l, \b --log <path-to-output-log-file><br>
    Path (absolute or relative) of the output log file.


See the output of the <tt>`opentrep-dbmgr --help'</tt> command for default options.


